    "name": "Soleil",
    "profile": "Since 1989, Soléil aka DJ MS aka Mike du Soléil\r\nspins the records in some of the most famous \r\nclubs in middle-germany like \"Strasse E\", \"Grotte\",\r\n\"Kilowatt\", \"Panzerhof\", \"Capitol\", \"Loreleil\", \r\n\"Musikfabrik\" and the middle-age catacombs at the elb\r\nwaterside.\r\nAlso, he has been resident DJ in europe's biggest\r\nopen air location called \"Megadrome\", where he\r\nconstantly fed thousands of partypeople with fresh\r\ntunes and a good mood. \r\n \r\nIn 1992, when he first met his later Jotown Records\r\npartner, he started his career as a producer of \r\nfinest techno and trance-tunes. As a former drummer \r\nhe never had problems to use the sparely options of a\r\ncommodore amiga to create some\r\nreally kickin' beats. Later on, he bought some hardware\r\nsynths and changed his Amiga to a PC, so that in 1996\r\nhis tracks where nearly 100% made on PC, only a few\r\nsamples still had the 8bit-charm of the good old Amiga.\r\n\r\nCurrently he moderates the radio show \"Monday Soundscape\"\r\n at spur1-dresden.de, [104,2",
